text:
This is a mid size shopping mall with a wide variety of shops selling a good variety of food, wares and services.

A typical neighborhood mall but I particularly like the cosy space where there are chairs and tables for shoppers to rest their tired feet, or to just chill for free. I hope it is not a temporary setup.

A bustling place with a good mix of shops. Recommended to visit if you are in the neighborhood.
Nice stuff... Beautiful shopping mall, with good restaurants too. Lovely pop up stores.

With the new TEL accessible to Parkway Parade, made it easily accessible to i12 or buses right in front of Roxy Square, just 5 mins walk either way.
After renovation and upgrading, unique vendors were housed within including SG hawker, never before a  food court was located.
If you’re looking for a healthy yet flavorful meal, Guzman y Gomez is a fantastic choice. Whether you’re a salad lover or just exploring healthier options, you’ll find something to enjoy here.
Nice and Clean Place! Lots of activities for kids on higher levels. The rock climbing zone is suitable for adults too. Not crowded on weekdays.
